| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `--elevated-focus-ring` | `0 0 0 3px var(--color-primary-ring), 0 0 0 1px var(--elevated-glass-border-strong)` |

## Component Treatment Pattern

### Gradient CTA Buttons (Primary, Danger, Success)
```css
[data-theme="elevated"] .acko-btn-primary {
  background: var(--elevated-primary-gradient);
  box-shadow: var(--elevated-primary-shadow);
  text-shadow: 0 1px 1px rgba(0,0,0,0.03);
}
[data-theme="elevated"] .acko-btn-primary::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute; inset: 0; border-radius: inherit;
  background: var(--elevated-convex-overlay);
  pointer-events: none;
}
```

### Glass Buttons (Secondary)
```css
[data-theme="elevated"] .acko-btn-secondary {
  background-color: var(--elevated-glass-bg);
  box-shadow: none;
  backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
}
```

### Border Gradient Buttons (Outline)
```css
[data-theme="elevated"] .acko-btn-outline {
  border: 1px solid transparent;
  background:
    linear-gradient(var(--elevated-glass-bg), var(--elevated-glass-bg)) padding-box,
    var(--elevated-border-gradient) border-box;
  backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
}
```

### Hover: translateY(-1px) lift
All elevated hover states add `transform: translateY(-1px)` for a subtle lift effect.

## Rules

- The elevated theme is light-background — global page stays white
- Only component chrome receives premium treatment
- Use `color-mix()` for glass transparency — avoids manual RGBA calculations
- All gradient CTA buttons need a `::before` convex overlay pseudo-element
- Keep `position: relative` on buttons so `::before` works (already in `.acko-btn`)
